name: Iowa State Football
summary: Iowa State University's football team is set to face Arizona State in the Big 12 Championship game. The matchup marks a historic moment for Iowa State, as it will be the first time the team has competed for the conference title. The Cyclones secured their spot in the championship game after an impressive 10-win season, which included a victory over rival Kansas State. Despite being ranked No. 16, Iowa State suffered a 45-19 loss to No. 12 Arizona State in the championship game.

name: Pearl Harbor day
summary: On December 7th, various commemorations and remembrances took place to mark the 83rd anniversary of the attack on Pearl Harbor. The Pacific Command held a ceremony honoring the past and passing the legacy to young service members, while the Department of Defense and Governor Newsom of California issued statements of remembrance. News outlets such as WDSU New Orleans, Hawaii News Now, and USA Today reported on the ceremonies and provided insights into the event's impact. In addition, official directives from the Governor's Offices of Florida and Kansas ordered flags to be flown half-staff in remembrance of the victims and survivors of the attack that brought the United States into World War II.

name: Man City
summary: In a crucial Premier League clash, Liverpool triumphed over defending champions Manchester City 2-0. Liverpool's victory extended their lead at the top of the standings to nine points, while City's struggles continued amidst questions about their form. Experts analyzed the game, highlighting City's defensive lapses and Liverpool's clinical finishing. Despite City's star striker Haaland, Liverpool exploited City's vulnerabilities, leading to a deeper examination of City's current crisis and Ederson's absence from the starting lineup. The match also provided livestreaming options for fans around the world. Liverpool's victory further cemented their dominance in the league, leaving City with much to ponder as they seek to regain their title-contending form.

name: Notre Dame Cathedral
summary: On April 16, 2023, five years after a devastating fire, Notre-Dame Cathedral in Paris reopened its doors to the public. The rebuilding process, which was supported by donations from around the world, saw the restoration of the cathedral's iconic architecture and interior, including the iconic Gargoyles. The grand reopening ceremony was attended by French President Emmanuel Macron, as well as religious leaders and international dignitaries, including former US President Donald Trump. The bells of the cathedral rang for the first time since the fire, and an archbishop formally restored the building to life. The reopening marked a significant milestone in the history of the cathedral, which has witnessed some of the most important events in French history.
